content: We met at DevDays and I was really excited to start working on the repo, is there any action that I'm missing?

Was there an issue list put together of things to address? I've got a really long lived fork of the fhir_parser that I've been neglecting mostly which I should get finished (added things like generating versions by name from the command line and a bunch of other things)
I don't remember where that list is? :-(
FYI: @Ilya Beda will present more details on the Beda fhir-py library at DevDays Amsterdam: http://www.devdays.com/amsterdam/schedule-2019/#event-725

I had a small PR in on the GitHub repo that hasn't been merged which caused me to wonder... if there's a list it would be cool to document it as issues in GitHub and I'll likely take some as time permits ;)
Github issues is the official list! Last I know is that @Harold Solbrig 's team is working on it.
Your two PRs look good to me, @Brian Kolowitz
Which is 'the' project? The fhir-parse or client-py?
I will try to organize a meet up at the HL7 wgm. And contact Harold so we can at least get a progress report
